  angular - front end development



  basic command
  1) To create project ng new projectname /     

  2) to run a project - ng serve / ng serve -- open
  
  3) to create  component - ng g c componentName


          basic concepts

   1) component- to create {html,css typescrip file} root component -app component

   2)module -to add libraries to  the project -root module - app module

   3) data binding -data sharing between html and css

               3.1 one way binding

                  3.1.1  component to view

                      3.1.1.1  string interpolation : syntax- {{variable name}}
                      3.1.1.2  property binding: syntax- [attributes]

                  3.1.2  view to component

                       3.1.2.1 event binding -syntax-(event)="function-call()"    
                       3.1.2.2 event binding using $event -syntax-(event)="function-call($event)" 
                       3.1.2.3 template referencing variable -syntax-#variable-name

               3.2 two way binding

                  3.2 using ngmodel-import formsModule in AppModule,
                  syntax: [(ngModule)]="variable-name"

 
   4) to set up path for a component :defined in the app routing in module 
                    syntax :{path:'',component:componentClassName}              

   5)dependency injuction-to share data between classes /diffrent components


   6)Angular Services-for reuse data   


   7)ngSubmit- to submit entire form-syntax-{ngSubmit}="function-call"

   8) Angular Forms
          
          8.1 Template Driven forms- first design html

          8.2 mode driven forms - first create model in ts
                  
                   8.2.1 Reactive Forms- Add Validation: ReactiveFormModule
                                    -form group-formBulder dependency inject,form array,form control

               